observations.recommendation:
To Municipal Accountant:
a. Observe the use of Perpetual Inventory Method pursuant to Section 114 of NGAS Manual in recording the Inventory account;
b. Record properly all purchases to its appropriate inventory account and maintain a supply ledger card for each type of inventory;
To Municipal Gen. Service Officer:
c. Maintain stock cards for supplies in your custody to account for the receipt and disposition of the same; and
d. Prepare Monthly Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued (MSSMI) duly supported by Requisition and Issuance Slip (RIS) from end-users for submission to the Accounting Office for proper recording of issuances of inventories.

To Municipal Accountant:
a. Exert more effort to come up with a record that will settle the differences with the property custodian/GSO records;
b. Compute for the depreciation charges of the identified PPEs and make the necessary adjustment on the affected accounts;
To Municipal Gen. Service Officer:
c. Conduct a complete inventory taking and submit the Report on Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) every January 31 of each year to the Office of the Auditor and ensure that items in RPCPPE are classified according to PPE type guided by the PPSAS-prescribed classification to facilitate easier reconciliation with the MAO;
d. Expedite the disposal of the above-mentioned unserviceable properties to reflect the accurate and reliable amount of the PPE account;
e. Direct the MAO to maintain property ledger cards to facilitate the reconciliation and recognition of depreciation expenses;
f. Direct the Inventory Committee to ensure that the reconciliation process between the physical inventory records of the MGSO and accounting records are properly in placed, to come up with a reliable report.

a. Provide an explanation and supporting documents for the memorandum, adjusting, and correcting entries made thereon. Henceforth, observe the proper usage of memorandum entry to avoid erroneous deductions. Also, ensure that adjusting and correcting entries are duly substantiated;
b. Follow the proper preparation of General Ledger and Subsidiary Ledger as found in Volume II of the Manual on the New Government Accounting System for Local Government Units;
c. Ensure consistency and accuracy in the recording of transactions. Observe proper charging of accounts, making sure that each account will only be used to its intended purpose;
d. Transfer the funds received from source agencies to Trust Fund in order to properly restrict and use them for the purpose for which the funds were received;
e. Henceforth, financial transactions should be recognized, recorded, and reported in the books in conformity with the Philippine Public Sector Accounting Standards (PPSAS). Apply the qualitative characteristics of information in financial reporting in order to make the information useful to users and support the achievements of the objectives of financial reporting.

a. Avail the compensatory time/days-off, in lieu of the overtime pay, or non-compensatory remuneration policy for overtime services rendered by employees, pursuant to CSC and DBM Joint Circular No. 2 s. 2004;
b. Strictly adhere to the provision of Section 305 of RA 7160 and avoid disbursements in excess of appropriation;
c. Observe the annual 5% of PS budget limitation on overtime pay and the required DBM authorization in case of excess annual overtime pay;
d. Conform to the overtime pay limit per personnel of 50% of basic annual salary. The accumulated overtime pay of every personnel of the agency should be monitored to facilitate compliance with this regulation;
e. Stop the practice of granting overtime pay to the department heads and assistant department heads in compliance with Item 6.0 of CSC and DBM JC No. 1 s. 2015;
f. Make sure that the authority to render overtime issued by the LCE specifically determines the priority activities that may warrant rendition of overtime services and the timing and duration thereof, the agency personnel who may be authorized to render overtime services, and the number of hours of overtime services and the manner of compensating the same in compliance with Item 5.0 of CSC and DBM JC No. 1 s. 2015;
g. Ensure that overtime services have proper and prior authorization before the conduct of the same and stated thereupon the detailed overtime work program and ensure that overtime claims shall be supported by quantified accomplishment report;
h. Formulate a detailed and systematic plan of activities per department. The planned activities shall integrate therewith the volume and frequency of regular and routine tasks to be performed to ensure that overtime services will be avoided; and
i. Require the Municipal Accounting Office in coordination with the Human Resource Management Office to ensure that withholding taxes in accordance with the Revised Withholding Tax Table are deducted from payments made in accordance with the above-mentioned regulations and that the same are remitted to the BIR within the prescribed period.

a. The management should implement the provisions of Sec. 305 of RA 7160 and endeavor to have a balanced budget in each fiscal year of operation;
b. Henceforth, the Local Finance Committee to adopt appropriate measures to control and monitor not only the appropriations and allotments but the cash availability as well. Ensure that 20% LDF, DRRMF, fund transfer from NGAs and other LGUs be utilized for the purpose for which the funds were intended; and
c. For the Local Finance Committee to consider different strategies to increase the Municipality’s income and intensify collection and impose cost-cutting measures and prioritize projects and programs.

a. Strengthen the LGU’s internal control system through planning of organization, segregation of custodial and accounting functions and installation of coordinated measures and procedures i.e., proper documentation, and proper procurement and use of the Philippine Government Electronic Procurement System;
b. The GSO/Designated Municipal Accountant and MBO to refrain from performing the duties of disbursing officer as the custodial, recording and reporting functions are incompatible and should be segregated and assigned to separate individuals to maintain principle of check and balance in the agency;
c. Stop granting additional cash advances to officials and employees until the previous ones have been liquidated and/or settled;

1. Direct the Inventory Committee to strategize the conduct of complete physical inventory taking of all the assets and properties of the LGU and ensure that items in RPCPPE are classified according to PPE type guided by the PPSAS-prescribed classification to facilitate easier reconciliation with the MAO;
2. Direct the MAO to maintain property ledger cards to facilitate the reconciliation and recognition of depreciation expenses;
3. Direct the Inventory Committee to ensure that the reconciliation process between the physical inventory records of the MGSO and accounting records are properly in placed, to come up with a reliable report.

1. Adopt other measure such as requesting monthly snapshot from the bank and follow up the enrollment to LBP’s “weAccess” online viewing facility to facilitate timely preparation and submission of bank reconciliation statements;
2. Recapture necessary information and determine the purpose of long outstanding bank debit and credit to memo. If found valid, prepare necessary adjusting entry in the books; 
3. Prepare journal entry voucher for the cancellation and reversion of stale checks and recognition of receivable from supplier due to overpayment; 
4. Henceforth, prepare a correct BRS and submit to the COA Auditor a copy of BRS supported by copies of the bank statements, JEV recording reconciling items that require correction in the books of accounts, as well as a copy of the letter to the respective bank informing them of errors noted in the BRS (other than those resulting from the timing of recording of transactions).

For BAC to:
1. Require each department/office to prepare PPMP for all PPAs for their respective departments/offices; 
2. Consolidate all Project Procurement Management Plans (PPMPs) into the Annual Procurement Plan (APP); 
3. Ensure compliance with RA 9184 by adopting competitive bidding, resorting to alternative methods of procurement only in highly exceptional cases, preparing RFQ and posting the invitation or request for submission of price quotation, as well as the other required documents, in the PhilGEPS website and the Procuring Entity's website and premises. 
For BAC and Accounting to:
4. Ensure all government transactions are duly supported with complete documentary requirements under COA Circular 2012-001 and other existing issuances of COA.

