a. Enforce the policy on waste segregation as mandated under RA 9003;
b. Expedite the construction of a sanitary landfill; and
c. Provide safety gears to the people assigned in waste collection.

We have recommended and Management agreed on the following:
Require the Municipal General Services Officer to maintain complete and updated property cards to facilitate periodic reconciliation with the Accounting unit;
Direct the Municipal General Services Officer to locate documents pertinent to the LGU properties preparatory to the conduct of the mandatory physical inventory;
Conduct physical counting of the LGU properties reflecting the actual status whether on hand per count, shortage, overage, missing, unserviceable and obsolete;
Submit an updated Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) to the Accounting Office for reconciliation with the latter's ledger cards, and furnish the same Report to the Office of the Auditor;
Maintain and update property records for periodical reconciliation with the Accounting records; and
Make appropriate and necessary adjustments in the books of accounts.
